TripAdvisor — Dataset
======================

SOURCE
------

Authority: TripAdvisor LLC (public website)
GraphQL endpoint: https://www.tripadvisor.com/data/graphql/ids
  (persisted-query endpoint; no API key required)
Session acquisition: Operator captures DataDome cookies + preRegisteredQueryId
  from a real logged-in browser (DevTools "Copy as cURL") and injects via
  POST /api/v1/tripadvisor/session. See OPERATOR GATE below and
  scripts/ta_bootstrap.py for the injection helper.

Data collected: destination listings (locationId, name, municipality, UF,
  review_count, rating, most_recent_review_at) and attraction listings (same
  fields plus parent location reference).

No TripAdvisor API partnership or data-licensing agreement is in place.
This source is operated under an accepted legal-risk posture (see LEGAL RISK).


CURRENT FILES
-------------

uf_geoids.json
    Maps each Brazilian UF abbreviation to TripAdvisor's internal geoId for
    that state. Used by TripAdvisorGraphQLClient to scope queries to one UF
    at a time and avoid full-site crawls.

    Source: manually compiled from TripAdvisor location pages (one-time lookup).
    Updated only when TripAdvisor changes their internal geoId assignments
    (very rare; requires manual verification).

    KNOWN CAVEAT — ES (Espírito Santo):
    During the 2026-06-24 spike, ES geoId 303516 was observed to redirect to
    MG (Minas Gerais, geoId 303380) on the TripAdvisor location page.
    The correct geoId for Espírito Santo on TripAdvisor may differ from 303516.
    Operators MUST verify this geoId before sweeping ES:
      1. Open https://www.tripadvisor.com/Tourism-g303516-Espirito_Santo_State-Vacations.html
      2. If the page redirects to MG, the ES geoId needs updating.
      3. Search TripAdvisor for "Espírito Santo" to find the real geoId.
      4. Update uf_geoids.json["ES"] with the confirmed geoId.
    The value 303516 is retained as a placeholder until confirmed.


LEGAL RISK
----------

TripAdvisor's Terms of Service, Section 5 ("Use of Site"), explicitly prohibit:
  - Systematic or automated data collection of any kind
  - Scraping, data mining, or harvesting content
  - Reproduction or redistribution of listings content without written permission

Using this source as implemented constitutes a Terms of Service violation and
exposes the operator to:
  - IP bans and DataDome/bot-detection challenges
  - Cease-and-desist legal communications
  - Account suspension if any TripAdvisor account is associated

This risk is DOCUMENTED AND ACCEPTED under the following conditions (see
MITIGATIONS and OPERATOR GATE). Operators must acknowledge this risk before
enabling the source.


MITIGATIONS
-----------

The following mitigations reduce exposure but do NOT eliminate the ToS violation:

(a) Low request rate — maximum one UF per minute; no continuous autonomous crawl.
    The sweep is deliberately slow and is never placed on the automated Celery beat.

(b) Residential proxy seam — brave/lanes/tripadvisor/client.py accepts a
    config.proxy_url parameter. Configuring a residential proxy shields the
    origin datacenter IP from TripAdvisor's datacenter-block heuristics.

(c) No PII stored — only aggregate review signals are persisted:
      review_count    (integer count of reviews)
      rating          (float average rating)
      most_recent_review_at  (datetime of the most recent review, no text)
    Author names, reviewer IDs, profile links, and review text are NEVER
    extracted, logged, or stored. TripAdvisorReviewSignals enforces
    extra="forbid" (Pydantic) to prevent future drift toward PII fields.

(d) Operator-gated sweep — the TripAdvisor sweep is NOT registered on the
    autonomous Celery beat. It requires an explicit engine start with
    source="tripadvisor" (POST /api/v1/engine/start). See OPERATOR GATE.

(e) Human promote-override — no automated path from TripAdvisor data to Mar.
    Every TA attraction that reaches DLQ requires a human steward action
    (promote_override) before the record can advance to Mar. This gives a
    human-review gate between scraped data and the canonical platform.


LGPD BASIS
----------

Legal basis: Legitimate interest (Art. 7º, IX, Lei 13.709/2018 — LGPD) in
territorial data quality for the Norteia platform.

Data minimisation applied: only aggregate review signals (review_count, rating,
most_recent_review_at) are stored. No individual reviewer data is processed,
retained, or transmitted. The LGPD basis applies exclusively to these aggregate
signals — not to any individual person's data.

TripAdvisorReviewSignals (brave/lanes/tripadvisor/schemas.py) enforces
model_config=ConfigDict(extra="forbid"). Any field that could identify an
individual (author, reviewer_id, review_text, profile_url, etc.) raises a
Pydantic ValidationError and is discarded before persistence.

No data subject rights obligations apply to this dataset because no personal
data is collected.


OPERATOR GATE
-------------

The TripAdvisor sweep is NOT enabled by default and does NOT run in CI.

To run a TripAdvisor sweep (Phase 12 session-injection model):

  1. Acknowledge legal risk (see LEGAL RISK above).

  2. Capture a session from a real logged-in browser:
       a. Open https://www.tripadvisor.com in your real Chrome/Firefox.
       b. Log in if prompted (DataDome is less aggressive for logged-in users).
       c. Open DevTools → Network tab.
       d. Navigate to any TripAdvisor state page (e.g., Bahia tourism).
       e. Find a POST to https://www.tripadvisor.com/data/graphql/ids.
       f. Right-click → "Copy as cURL". Save the cURL command.

  3. Inject the session via scripts/ta_bootstrap.py:
       python scripts/ta_bootstrap.py \
         --curl-file /path/to/captured_curl.sh \
         --endpoint http://localhost:8000

     Or POST directly:
       POST /api/v1/tripadvisor/session
       Authorization: Bearer <steward-token>
       Content-Type: application/json
       {
         "cookies": {"datadome": "...", "TASession": "..."},
         "query_ids": {"destinations": "<hex-id>", "attractions": "<hex-id>"},
         "user_agent": "Mozilla/5.0 ...",
         "acquired_at": "2026-06-24T12:00:00Z"
       }

     The endpoint runs a canary check before writing to Redis. If the session
     is invalid, it returns 422 with reason=invalid_session.

  4. (Optional) Configure a residential proxy:
       BRAVE_TA_PROXY_URL=socks5://user:pass@proxy-host:port

  5. Start the sweep via the engine API:
       POST /api/v1/engine/start
       Content-Type: application/json
       {"source": "tripadvisor", "depth": "NASCENTE_RIO"}

The sweep does NOT run automatically. It is NOT scheduled on the Celery beat.
CI and offline tests never set RUN_REAL_EXTERNALS — all TripAdvisor client
calls are handled by NullTripAdvisorClient (brave/clients/null_tripadvisor.py);
unit tests use FakeTripAdvisorClient (tests/fakes/fake_tripadvisor.py).
